Special Characters Cheatsheet
@    Ampersat, at symbol
&     Ampersand
#     Hash
~     Tilde
!      Exclamation mark
?     Question mark
^     Caret
'      Single quote
"     Double quote
(     Left parenthesis, ) Right parenthesis, () Parenthese
{     Left curly bracket, } Right curly bracket, {} Curly brackets
[     Left bracket, ] Right bracket, [] Brackets
:     Colon
;     Semicolon
<    Less than
>    Greater than
=    Equals
|     Pipe
/     Slash
\     Backslash
-     Dash, minus
_     Underscore
*     Asterisk
$     Dollar sign
%    Percent sign

Coding Shortcuts
To further speed up your development speed, there are some common shortcuts you can use with text editors like Visual Studio Code.

Windows
General Shortcuts
ctrl + s: Save document (SUPER IMPORTANT!!!)
ctrl + c: Copy (SUPER IMPORTANT!!!)
ctrl + v: Paste (SUPER IMPORTANT!!!)
ctrl + x: Cut (be careful with this one, use copy instead always when can)
ctrl + a: Select all text
ctrl + b: Make selected text bold
ctrl + u: Make selected text italic

Text Editing
home: Move cursor to start of line
end: Move cursor to end of line
ctrl + left: Move cursor to left of current word
ctrl + right: Move cursor to right of current word
ctrl + up: Move cursor to starting of file
ctrl + down: Move cursor to end of file

Add shift to any of these to combinations to select text.

